When importing users from LDAP directory that contains mixed case usernames, users receive the following error:

{noformat}
2008-10-27 13:18:04,797 http-8095-3 ERROR [integration.directory.internal.InternalDirectory] Cannot add invalid principal mixedCase
com.atlassian.crowd.integration.exception.InvalidPrincipalException: Invalid principal username: mixedCase. Username must be lower case.
{noformat}

We need to toLower those values for import into a delegated directory.

If users attempt an Atlassian user/group import in Crowd, they receive the following error in the logs:

{noformat}
2008-10-15 21:05:35,289 TP-Processor1 INFO [atlassian.xwork.interceptors.SafeParametersInterceptor] Attempt to call unsafe property setter configuration.password on com.atlassian.crowd.console.action.dataimport.AtlassianImporter@xxxxxx
{noformat}

and errors regarding directory selection on the import screen.

{code}
catch (InvalidAuthenticationException e)
{
  throw new InvalidAuthenticationException(SOAPService.INVALID_AUTHENTICATION);
}
{code}

This overwrites the message set by the directory and, as a bonus, is factually incorrect.

Workaround: use {{authenticatePrincipal()}}.

