If I enter a 500 user license in a Crowd 1.5 (trunk) instance that has 2000 users, I am allowed to update the license and am told the update was successful.  If I attempt to revert to my unlimited license, I receive the screen I should have gotten on the first update warning me about my 500 user license:

{noformat}
Your current license does not permit the number of users you have configured in Crowd, please upgrade to a new license, or contact Atlassian Sales Support.
{noformat}

We should post the warning on the first update and not accept/commit the license at all if it does not meet the current user total.

